(53, 'How Trade Schools Train You For Business', 'For people interested in starting their own business, getting a degree from a trade school is a great way to gain skills for working in a specialized industry. Whether you’re training to become an expert in computers or an electrician,Do IT For Me Tech Community shares how trade schools offer accelerated and immersive programs that can give you the skills you need to become an entrepreneur in your field.', 'business, Business knowledge, business plan, DIFM, entrepreneur, pandemic', 7, 1, 'https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/How+Trade+Schools+Train+You+For+Business.jpg', '<p><br><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-d406e982-7fff-4cfc-933c-c556ab4f225a\"><span style=\"font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 11pt;\">For people interested in starting their own business, getting a degree from a trade school is a great way to gain skills for working in a specialized industry. Whether you’re training to become an expert in computers or an electrician,</span><a href=\"https://difm.tech/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\"><span style=\"font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(17, 85, 204); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 11pt;\">Do IT For Me Tech Community</span></a><span style=\"font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 11pt;\"> shares how trade schools offer accelerated and immersive programs that can give you the skills you need to become an entrepreneur in your field.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></strong></p><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-d406e982-7fff-4cfc-933c-c556ab4f225a\"><span style=\"font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">Getting a trade school education&nbsp;</span></strong></h2><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-d406e982-7fff-4cfc-933c-c556ab4f225a\"><span style=\"font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 11pt;\">Trade schools can be a great option for those who want to minimize their time in the classroom and start working sooner. One of the benefits of learning at a trade school is that you can skip general education courses and get right into specific skill training. Students at trade schools typically experience small class sizes and one-on-one training with instructors, unlike massive university lectures in which you’re one of several hundred students. You’ll be more likely to gain skills quickly through such individualized attention, and you’ll be learning alongside like-minded peers.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-d406e982-7fff-4cfc-933c-c556ab4f225a\"><span style=\"font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 11pt;\">One notable benefit of a trade school education is the likelihood of finding a job soon after graduating. Trade schools often have career counselors who work to help graduates find employment, making it easier to earn money right away. The typical trade school education is also relatively short. Many will finish their training within two years.&nbsp;</span></strong></p><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-d406e982-7fff-4cfc-933c-c556ab4f225a\"><span style=\"font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">From trade school to business development&nbsp;</span></strong></h2><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-d406e982-7fff-4cfc-933c-c556ab4f225a\"><span style=\"font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 11pt;\">Recent graduates from trade schools have a great opportunity to become entrepreneurs. Having such a specialized education immediately puts trade school graduates at an advantage: you’ll be able to advance your career with enough training to earn money right away.&nbsp; For example, if you’ve just learned to become an IT expert, you can start advertising your services to individuals or businesses as soon as you get licensed in your state. Starting a business is a great way to begin earning money quickly, and is a relatively straightforward path for recent graduates.&nbsp;</span></strong></p><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-d406e982-7fff-4cfc-933c-c556ab4f225a\"><span style=\"font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">Starting a business&nbsp;</span></strong></h2><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-d406e982-7fff-4cfc-933c-c556ab4f225a\"><span style=\"font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 11pt;\">Even if you have all the skills to successfully do business in your industry, there are important business development steps you’ll need to take before launching. It is important to determining what licensing you will need to run your business in your state. Also, it is vital to form the right business structure. Many trade-based companies will opt for a limited liability company or LLC, which provides a simple tax structure and will protect personal assets in case of a lawsuit. Another key to your business’s future is a business plan. Laying out a map for your goals is a good way to formalize your expectations. Plus it conveys to lenders that you’re serious about what you’re doing.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-d406e982-7fff-4cfc-933c-c556ab4f225a\"><span style=\"font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 11pt;\">Keep in mind that if you want to expand your business knowledge, earning an accounting degree is an option. This degree will teach you how to evaluate financial data and reports which could be invaluable for your business. If you enroll in an online program, you’ll have the flexibility to learn as you continue to run your business.&nbsp;</span></strong></p><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-d406e982-7fff-4cfc-933c-c556ab4f225a\"><span style=\"font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 24px;\">Running a business during a pandemic&nbsp;</span></strong></h2><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-d406e982-7fff-4cfc-933c-c556ab4f225a\"><span style=\"font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 11pt;\">Starting a business involves jumping through a number of hoops. Given the current COVID-19 pandemic, business owners will have to take additional steps. An as much as possible virtually to reduce the health risks and operate safely. Renovators, electricians, and plumbers, it is important to keep both yourself and residents safe during your work. Check in with customers about their level of comfortability. Also, give residents plenty of notice so they can clear out. That will let you do your job with minimal social contact if they need to take precautions.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></strong></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;\"><strong style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-d406e982-7fff-4cfc-933c-c556ab4f225a\"><span style=\"font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 11pt;\">Also, becoming an entrepreneur is a great idea for trade school graduates. With specialized skills tradespeople can jump into their careers right away. As you set up your business, remember to get the proper licenses. Also, set up a business structure that will protect both you and your business. And if you need extra monetary support to get started, consider applying for small business financial help from the government.</span></strong></p>', 0, '2021-09-08 09:00:00', '2024-12-19 10:06:44', 'how-trade-schools-train-you-for-business', ''),
