(99, 'Introduction to Web Development', 'Web programming is another name for Web Development. We have seen many interactive websites such as Facebook, E-commerce websites like Amazon, Flipkart, etc. some of the amazing websites which handle more than millions of servers. Work that mainly involves developing a website for an intranet(a private network) and the World Wide Web. The task includes Web design, client-side/server-side scripting, network security configuration client liaison, and Web server, Web Development considers being one of the good professions because it helps to improve problem-solving skills, experiment with new technologies, and building useful and interactive things. Generally, it refers to the main non-design aspects of building Web sites: writing coding and markup. Content Management System (CMS) uses to make content available with basic technical skills and changes easier by Web developers.', 'CSS, HTML, JS, Web developers, web development, WordPress', 9, 1, 'https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/Introduction+to+Web+Development.jpeg', '<p>Web programming is another name for Web Development. We have seen many interactive websites such as Facebook, E-commerce websites like Amazon, Flipkart, etc. some of the amazing websites which handle more than millions of servers. Work that mainly involves developing a website for an intranet(a private network) and the World Wide Web.<br><br>The task includes Web design, client-side/server-side scripting, network security configuration client liaison, and Web server, Web Development considers being one of the good professions because it helps to improve problem-solving skills, experiment with new technologies, and building useful and interactive things. Generally, it refers to the main non-design aspects of building Web sites: writing coding and markup. Content Management System (CMS) uses to make content available with basic technical skills and changes easier by Web developers.</p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/introduction-to-web-development/Introduction%20to%20Web%20Development%201.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Who are Web Developers?</strong><br><br>Creating and maintaining the website is the responsibility of Web developers. They work for the clients to bring up specific services or products onto the web. Therefore, the client can be the organization, government, or tech company. For businesses and larger organizations, the team consists of hundreds of web developers. While developing Web sites, they follow standard methods like Agile methodologies.<br><br>Smaller organizations may only require a contracting developer or single permanent, or secondary assignment. This is to related job positions such as information systems technician or graphic designer. Rather than the domain of a designated department, web development may be a collaborative effort between departments.<br><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Practical Web Development</strong></p><p><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Basic</strong><br><br>In practice, basic interdisciplinary skills/roles require in many Web developers will have, including:<br><br>Web design/Graphic design It includes copyediting/copywriting with web accessibility, usability, and search engine optimization in information architecture<br><br>Mobile responsiveness<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Testing Software Testing</span><br><br>The component(s) with the intent to find whether the specified requirements it satisfies or not or the process of evaluating a system known as Testing. In order to identify any errors, gaps, or missing requirements contrary to the actual requirements testing is executing a system. The extent of testing varies greatly between developers, organizations, and individual applications or sites.</p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/introduction-to-web-development/Introduction%20to%20Web%20Development%202.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Open Source Environment</span><br><br>Perl/Plack, GlassFish, LAMP (Linux, Apache, MySQL, PHP) stack, and BerkeleyDB are some of the famous open-source tools for Web Development. To learn web development cost is not high and it is minimum. To the growth of the industry, another contributing factor has been the rise of easy-to-use WYSIWYG Web-development software, such as BlueGriffon, Adobe Dreamweaver, and Microsoft Visual Studio. Learning Web development is easy as many sources are available on the other sites. Some of the common languages one can learn quickly is HTML(Hypertext Markup Language), CSS(Cascading Style Sheets), and JS(JavaScript).<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Dynamic Websites</span><br><br>For developers to build more interactive Web sites and dynamic, an ever-growing set of tools and technologies have helped. Further, As Web services were traditionally only available as applications on a desk-based computer web developers now help to deliver applications. For many opportunities to decentralize media distribution and information it allows. With the rise of cloud services, examples in day-to-day life are such as Dropbox, Adobe Creative Cloud, and Google Drive. From many locations, for their application environment instead of being tied to a specific workstation, these Web services allow users to interact with applications.<br><br>Examples of dramatic transformation in commerce and communication led by Web Development include e-commerce. The way consumers find and purchase services and goods online retailers such as Amazon.com and Buy.com (among many others) have transformed the shopping and bargain-hunting experience for many consumers. For individual Web sites, Web development is the blog is another example of transformative communication led.</p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/introduction-to-web-development/Introduction%20to%20Web%20Development%203.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br>Web applications such as Movable Type and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WordPress\" target=\"_blank\">WordPress</a> blog environment are very interactive and user-friendly. In marketing and personal networking, web development has a remarkable role. For work or for commerce but serve more broadly for communication and social networking, websites are no longer simply tools. Web sites such as Twitter and Facebook provide users with a platform to communicate and interactive way to engage the public and organizations with a more personal.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Conclusion</span><br><br>Web development is one of the vastly used technology. People are dependent on it for their daily activities services and products. In Web development, having a good wireframe and designing it specifically makes websites more interactive. Many people have changed their career domain towards web development.<br><br>To read more articles, <a href=\"https://difm.llc/insight\">click here</a></p>', 1, '2021-07-27 09:00:00', '2024-12-19 10:06:44', 'introduction-to-web-development', ''),
(100, 'Why Did Facebook Introduce Oculus AR?', 'Oculus. Heard of it? Anyway, one does not miss the name ‘Facebook’ when it comes to counting the most popular and best internet services all over the globe as it constitutes the four best internet service providers- Google, Amazon, Apple, and Facebook. However, people often mistake Facebook as just a social media site for connections and communal interaction but Facebook does not limit itself there.', 'Augmented Reality, entertainment, Facebook, future, gaming, innovation, oculus, products, technology', 7, 1, 'https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/Why+Did+Facebook+Introduce+Oculus+AR.jpg', '<p>Oculus. Heard of it? Anyway, one does not miss the name ‘Facebook’ when it comes to counting the most popular and best internet services all over the globe as it constitutes the four best internet service providers- Google, Amazon, Apple, and Facebook. However, people often mistake Facebook as just a social media site for connections and communal interaction but Facebook does not limit itself there.</p><p><br>Nonetheless, Facebook is an American multinational company with more than 2.8 billion active users per month. It is one of the leading companies that provide the best Internet services. Somehow, the question that begs is still the fact that what is the connection between Facebook, and virtual reality? Read the article to find the answer to this question in the best and most simple manner.</p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/why-did-facebook-introduce-oculus-ar/Why%20Did%20Facebook%20Introduce%20Oculus%20AR%201.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Introduction to Oculus VR</strong><br><br>Oculus is a subsidiary of the internet tech giant Facebook. The brand was burdened with the responsibility to produce virtual reality headsets which are exceptionally designed for video gaming, 3D reconstruction, entertainment, live events, fitness, and more for gamers and developers.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">History and Invention</span><br><br>The founding family of Oculus VR includes Palmer Luckey, Brendan Iribe, Michael Antonov, and Nate Michelle in July 2012 in California. Palmer’s eagerness to earn a reputation for having a personal and huge collection of head-mounted displays that were effective, popular, and inexpensive lead to the creation of Oculus. The company aims and promotes the concept to ‘live the unbelievable’. It is majorly popular for its headsets, games, and headset accessories.<br><br>Within 2 years, Facebook-owned Oculus with the motive to strengthen its game industry figures and mixed reality creations. The commencement of Rift, a virtual reality headset designed for video gaming purposes was the stepping stone in the journey of the Oculus. In 2015, Oculus VR owned Surreal Vision, a British startup. Furthermore, the company partnered with Samsung to develop the Samsung Gear VR for the Samsung Galaxy smartphones. In 2016, the company launched its first consumer headset known as the Oculus Rift CV1. The product specialized in incorporating wonderfully assembled VR displays, audios, and tracking systems. Additionally, the recent product launched by Oculus is the Oculus Quest 2.</p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/why-did-facebook-introduce-oculus-ar/Why%20Did%20Facebook%20Introduce%20Oculus%20AR%202.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Products</strong></p><p><br><strong style=\"font-size: 18px;\">1 Gear VR</strong><br><br>Oculus VR collaborated with Samsung Electronics to develop Samsung Gear VR in 2015. It is an AR simulation headset that uses the assistance of a viable Samsung Galaxy gadget that goes about as the headset\'s showcase and processor, while the Gear VR unit itself goes about as the regulator and some different devices. The Samsung Gear VR is a truly outstanding and least expensive approaches to encounters computer-generated reality if you own a Samsung cell phone. Notwithstanding, Oculus\' desire of zeroing in on itself and its items turned into the preeminent explanation behind the discontinuity of Gear.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">2 Oculus Go</span><br><br>Facebook Technologies in organization with Qualcomm and Xiaomi fostered an independent virtual reality headset, the Oculus Go in 2018. The Go contains every one of the vital parts to give AR encounters and does not require any fastening to an outside gadget to utilize. The headset utilizes the Android versatile working framework and incorporates applications for watching both conventional and vivid video and different media from different sources. Go rejuvenates encounters in rich detail and lively shading with top-tier imaginative focal points. Additionally, its ergonomic plan, underlying sound, and simple-to-work and control offices make it an incredible item.</p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/why-did-facebook-introduce-oculus-ar/Why%20Did%20Facebook%20Introduce%20Oculus%20AR%203.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">3 Oculus Rift</span><br><br>Rift was dispatched in 2016 that end up being effective. It is an AR experience headset with the intention to associate with a powerful PC to empower complex calculations and illustration delivery. The framework\'s Constellation situating innovation utilizes look following and IR LED sensors to distinguish the client\'s position while associating with the virtual climate. Besides, its screening and highlights pulled in many. Be that as it may, the framework requires an elite PC. Additionally, the organization has reported stopping expressing that it needs to zero in on Oculus Quest 2.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">4 Quest</span><br><br>Oculus has a scope of Quest with the first being dispatched in 2019, and the second, Oculus Quest 2 was dispatched as of late.<br><br><strong>• Oculus Quest</strong><br><br>It is an independent VR simulation headset that can run games and programming remotely under an Android depending working framework. The Oculus Quest got acclaim at its cost and comfort. Also, for having worked on graphical loyalty and following over Go. However, Go was prospected front-substantial form and downsized illustrations quality over PC-based VR games. An across-the-board headset is easy and handy to set up. Additionally, it has understanding following, underlying sound, hand following, and two touch regulators, all of which represent its prosperity.</p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/why-did-facebook-introduce-oculus-ar/Why%20Did%20Facebook%20Introduce%20Oculus%20AR%204.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br></p><p><strong>• Oculus Quest 2</strong><br><br>Similarly, as with its archetype, the Quest 2 is fit for running as both an independent headset with an interior, according to the Android working framework, and with Oculus-viable VR programming running on a personal computer when in association with USB or Wi-Fi. Also, it is the high-level rendition of its archetype with various highlights. Some examples are progressed handling power, wonderful development regulators, simple arrangement, and extraordinary presentation and sound.<br><br>To read more articles, <a href=\"https://difm.llc/insight\">click here.</a><br></p>', 1, '2021-07-27 09:00:00', '2024-12-19 10:06:44', 'why-did-facebook-introduce-oculus-ar', ''),
(101, 'Will Blockchain be the future?', 'All types of cryptocurrencies make use of distributed ledger technology known as Blockchain. For recording and documenting transactions that take place blockchain, acts as decentralized systems involving a particular digital currency. Maintaining identical copies across each member\'s computer within a network blockchain is a transaction ledger. Therefore, to facilitate the security of the blockchain, across each part of the network helps the ledger distributes.', 'Applications, blockchain, blockchain technology, cryptocurrencies, cryptocurrencies technology, future', 5, 1, 'https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/Will+Blockchain+be+the+future.jpg', '<p>All types of cryptocurrencies make use of distributed ledger technology known as Blockchain. For recording and documenting transactions that take place blockchain, acts as decentralized systems involving a particular digital currency. Maintaining identical copies across each member\'s computer within a network blockchain is a transaction ledger. Therefore, to facilitate the security of the blockchain, across each part of the network helps the ledger distributes.</p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/will-blockchain-be-the-future/Will%20Blockchain%20be%20the%20future%201.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br>In late 2017 and early 2018, in the general financial and investment worlds, Bitcoin and other cryptocurrencies grew intensely popular. A niche area for cryptocurrency enthusiasts since become more. The most important innovation to come out of the cryptocurrency boom is blockchain technology may ultimately see. However, across a host of industries blockchain technology remains a quickly-growing area of growth for companies.<br><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Blockchain Basics</strong><br><br>Parties may be able to view previous ledger entries and record new entries, depending upon the blockchain. By powerful cryptography, the contents and the blocks within them protect. This ensures that previous transactions within the network cannot be either destroyed or forge. In conclusion, to maintain a trusted transaction network without relying on a central authority blockchain technology allows a digital currency.</p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/will-blockchain-be-the-future/Will%20Blockchain%20be%20the%20future%202.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br>Digital currencies are the reason for the process of decentralization. Additionally, over the past several years, in facilitating the rise of digital currencies blockchain is most famous for its role. With a specific cryptocurrency or if it utilizes in any number of other applications it\'s likely that financial advisors and many others in the investing world will encounter blockchain technology much more in the years to come, whether it links.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Payments</span><br><br>For payments taking place across international borders, the transfer of value has been both slow and expensive. In multiple locations, before the intended recipient can collect his or her, money the transfer process typically requires the participation of multiple banks involves multiple currencies. To help facilitate this process in a faster way, but these tend to be quite expensive there are some services.</p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/will-blockchain-be-the-future/Will%20Blockchain%20be%20the%20future%203.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br>A much faster and cheaper alternative to traditional cross-border payments methods blockchain technology has the potential to provide. Therefore, in different parts of the world and security concerns, some hurdles pass, including the regulation of cryptocurrencies. Moreover, areas of blockchain technology application this is one of the most promising and talked about.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24