ructure of secure networks which allows users to make transactions whenever they want. The whole structure is a digital ledger where a decentralized system takes place in the Blockchain. A correct private key and hash key for every block will allow continuing to grow a big chain of blocks. Every detail of the transactions is a showcase to the people without fear when the double-spend attack occurs. In the future, surely blockchain technology will be something that every country and people will follow.<br><br>To read more articles, <a href=\"https://difm.llc/insight/page/1\">click here</a></p>', 1, '2021-07-12 09:00:00', '2024-12-19 10:06:44', 'prominent-applications-of-blockchain', ''),
(113, 'Explore the Google Suite', 'Suite. What comes to your mind when you hear the word ‘Suite’? A suite in any form of public accommodation, which can be a cruise, hotel, or any other place is a set of rooms dedicated to one person or one family, or one group for a particular purpose. Similarly, Google Suite refers to a workspace that provides you with different tools and products that are dedicated to one goal. Think of it as a collection of various tools, software, and products to enhance your productivity, collaboration, and creativity.', 'calendar, chat, docs, drive, forms, google, meet, sheets, sites, slides, suite, workspace', 7, 1, 'https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/Explore+the+Google+Suite+1.jpg', '<p>Suite. What comes to your mind when you hear the word ‘Suite’? A suite in any form of public accommodation, which can be a cruise, hotel, or any other place is a set of rooms dedicated to one person or one family, or one group for a particular purpose. Similarly, Google Suite refers to a workspace that provides you with different tools and products that are dedicated to one goal. Think of it as a collection of various tools, software, and products to enhance your productivity, collaboration, and creativity.<br><br>Google Suite is more often known as the Google Workspace now. It is a collection of cloud computing facilities, tools, and software required for production, collaboration, and innovation. It was first introduced in 2006 and it has been popular ever since.</p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/explore-the-google-suite/Explore%20the%20Google%20Suite.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Benefits of the Google Workspace</strong><br><br>The question arises that why should we use Google Workspace? Nonetheless, there are many answers to that. The list is as follows:<br><br><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong>1. Boost your business</strong></span><br><br>Google Workspace or the Google Suite provides you with a variety of tools that help you to improve and enhance your business. Besides, irrespective of whether it is communication, documentation, file management, or organization, Google Workspace does it all for you. It helps you in promoting as well as growing your business. Furthermore, it provides you with commercial email addresses with your domain name attached to them. As a result, that adds to the brand value of the company.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">2. Storage</span><br><br>Google workspace provides you with enough storage to manage your personal affairs. However, the storage provided is not sufficient for business or commercial purposes but Google offers a better alternative for the problem such as their various plans and packages with amazing deals and offers that benefit you.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">3. Security</span><br><br>A brand as popular as Google dominates the market because it understands the value and importance of individual data and privacy. Therefore, Google promises zero risks of data security. Google Workspace is highly secure and you can be relieved about your documents and information.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">4. Accessibility</span><br><br>The tools provided by Google in its Google Suite are compatible, available, and accessible. In simple words, that means that you can access these tools from any device with just the help of your Google account. Furthermore, all of these tools are interlinked and that makes you feel confident about your data.</p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/explore-the-google-suite/Explore%20the%20Google%20Suite%20.3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br>Further advantages of Google Workspace are that it provides you with migration tools and 24/7 customer support. Also, it is cost-effective, fast, and robust, and probably the best solution and the one-stop destination for all your problems.<br><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Products and Tools as a Part of the Google Suite</strong><br><br>Here is the list of the ten most popular Google Workspace Tools<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">1. Gmail</span><br><br>Gmail is a free email communication service with more than 1.8 billion active users worldwide. It can help you send, receive, spam, classify and flag and delete emails in any way you want.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">2. Google Drive</span><br><br>Google Drive is a free file storage and syncing service that allows users to store access, and sync files at will. Besides, Google Drive has more than 1 billion active users around the world.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">3. Google Docs, Sheets, and Slides</span><br><br>These are all a part of the free web Google Docs Editing Suite. They are the most suitable online alternatives to MS Word, Excel, and PowerPoint. They allow multiple users to access the same file at the same time. In addition, it promises strict data security.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">4. Google Forms</span><br><br>This is survey management software that is part of the free web Google Docs Edition package. It can help you create your forms and surveys to collect the necessary information. It has functions such as data analysis and presentation<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">5. Google Sites</span><br><br>Google Sites is a re-included, structured, free wiki and web page creation tool that is part of the free web-based Google Docs Editing Suite. Users can create their website regardless of their coding base.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">6. Google Calendar</span><br><br>With the Google Calendar app, you can reduce the time it takes to manage certain things, so you can keep track of your schedule, simplify your work and spend a lot of time enjoying your schedule.</p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/explore-the-google-suite/explore%20the%20google%20suits%204.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">7. Google Chat</span><br><br>It is a communication software that can provide direct messages and team chat rooms and various other facilities for your team<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">8. Google Meet</span><br><br>It is a free image communication service that allows about 100 participants to join the conference room at the same time. One of the two applications that make up the Google Hangouts alternative, the other is Google Chat<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">9. Google Current</span><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">s</span><br><br>Currents is highly beneficial by all Google workspace users for corporate internal communications.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">10. Google Keep</span><br><br>Google Keep is a note-taking service included back in the free web-based Google Docs Editing Suite. You can create notes and share them with others.<br><br>To read more articles, <a href=\"https://difm.llc/insight/page/1\">click here.</a></p>', 1, '2021-07-12 09:00:00', '2024-12-19 10:06:44', 'explore-the-google-suite', ''),
(114, 'Power of Bitcoin', 'Yes, you heard it right. Sneaky coins with a trillion-dollar market cap opened up new horizons for humanity, teaching us the art of creating money from thin air. There are approximately 4000 different cryptocurrencies in the market. Some are economically viable, while others are like selling your soul to demons. Eager to please Santoshi updated its logo design in February 2010 rifling on the Thai Baht concept the revised Logo depicts the new famous with two vertical strokes.', '	bitcoin, blockchain, cryptocurrencies', 7, 1, 'https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/Power+of+Bitcoin+6.jpg', '<p>Yes, you heard it right. Sneaky coins with a trillion-dollar market cap opened up new horizons for humanity, teaching us the art of creating money from thin air. There are approximately 4000 different cryptocurrencies in the market. Some are economically viable, while others are like selling your soul to demons. Eager to please Santoshi updated its logo design in February 2010 rifling on the Thai Baht concept the revised Logo depicts the new famous with two vertical strokes.</p><br><p>For each cryptocurrency, there is one key element that makes it all possible, the Blockchain. In simple terms, a growing list of records known as blocks links together using cryptocurrency. Challenging Authority, shaking nerves of traditional investors, crazy market cap, and cult-like following around the world are some of the gold achievements in the crown of cryptocurrencies.</p><br><p><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Why should we buy Bitcoin?</strong></p><br><p>If the bank can kick out the president, they can do it for you too, and they will. Be your bank before your bank decides to kick you out. However, Bitcoin supply limits to 21,000,000. In other words, it requires lots of work to produce another. Still, it is on foot compared to the Global economy.</p><br><p>Citizens or banks owning cryptocurrencies governments have mixed policies on the legality. In several industries, China has implemented blockchain technology including a national digital currency that launched in the year 2020. In addition, Western governments including the European Union and the United States have initiated similar projects so they can strengthen their respective currencies.</p><br><p><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/power-of-bitcoin/power%20of%20bitcoin%202.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">How much electricity consumption takes place in Bitcoin?</span></p><br><p>On the notion of an immutable ledger, called the blockchain, Bitcoin and most other cryptocurrencies founded. The transfers of value from one party to another it comprises. To a kind of algorithmic puzzle that fits a very specific set of requirements cryptocurrency \"miners\" seek results.</p><br><p>A server finds an acceptable solution, every ten minutes on average, and from the bitcoin system, the miner gets a reward. In transaction fees, they get $1000 and 12.5 bitcoins which are approximate of value $85000. To the blockchain, the miner\'s combination of transactions and solutions was added. Therefore, the longest of the block will be the winning factor.</p><br><br><p><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/power-of-bitcoin/Power%20of%20Bitcoin%203.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br></p><p>They also have to ensure that coins cannot mints too quickly. Here the most important thing for the miner is the ability to work in competition. The more electricity used by the computer networks computational network to get increases. In other words, it is a relation between creating bitcoins and the electricity required.</p><br><p>The electricity of the year consumed by the network of Bitcoin was found to be about 30 terawatt-hours (TWh). According to de Vries\'s estimates, between 78TWh and 101TWh, or about the same as Norway, currently, the network uses more than twice as much energy. In the process of transaction nearly, nearly 300 kg of carbon dioxide. By 750,000 credit cards swiped, the equivalent to the carbon footprint produced.</p><br><p><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/power-of-bitcoin/Power%20of%20Bitcoin%204.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br></p><br><p><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Calculating the Cost</span></p><br><br><p>This paragraph lets us understand how to calculate the electrical energy used to power the bitcoin network.</p><br><br><p>1.) To solve the puzzles, calculate how many sums conducts per second.</p><br><br><p>2.) Then find out how much electricity it takes to do each sum. The sums are known as hashes. In this process, so many hashes take place like for million it is megahashes and billion it is gigahashes respectively. In early 2020, with close to 120 exam hashes per second, the computers on the bitcoin network were cranking out.</p><br><br><p>One petahash is a quadrillion hash per second, one terahash is a trillion hashes per second, and one exahash is one quintillion hashes per second. Various bitcoin-mining computers are available out there. But (ASIC) mining computers i.e. Application-Specific Integrated Circuit focused on most of the companies. To conduct their calculations, they require less energy.</p><br><br><p><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/power-of-bitcoin/Power%20of%20Bitcoin%205.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br></p><p>Businesses claim to use only one watt of power for every gigahash per second of computing while mining companies run lots of ASIC miners as performed when mining for bitcoins. Here\'s how energy use relates to hashtag volume.</p><br><br><p>One Exahash Per Second = One Gigawatt</p><br><br><p>One Petahash Per Second = One Megawatt</p><br><br><p>One Terahash Per Second = One Kilowatt</p><br><br><p>One Gigahash Per Second = One Watt</p><br><br><p>Above all, it takes 10 minutes to mine no matter how many miners would be present. To mine a bitcoin using the average power usage provided by ASIC miners it will take 72,000 GW (or 72 Terawatts) of power 600 seconds (10 minutes), all else being equal. In conclusion, it is fairly efficient to have one watt per&nbsp;<a href=\"https://coinrivet.com/guides/cryptocurrencies/what-is-hash-rate/\" target=\"_blank\">gigahash&nbsp;</a>per second. So, this is somewhat a conservative estimate. Many residential miners use more power.</p><br><p><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/power-of-bitcoin/Power%20of%20Bitcoin%201.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Conclusion:</span></p><br><p>Bitcoin extracts the price in terms of energy use and environmental impact. Depending on this depends on how useful it will be to society. Judging an ever-moving target is hard. Similarly, to serve more people in the market the interest in Bitcoin continues to rise, which in turn leads to more power used.</p><br><br><p>To read more articles,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://difm.tech/introduction-to-blockchain-technology\">click here</a></p>', 1, '2021-07-10 09:00:00', '2024-12-19 10:06:44', 'power-of-bitcoin', '');
