><p><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Popular Tools</strong></p><p><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><br></strong><strong>1. Gboard</strong><br><br>The Google keyboard is like any other keyboard, helping you type to save queries or input. Moreover, it allows you to search on Google. This capability of Google Keyboard is different from regular keyboards that only allow users to type. Google Keyboard will remember your data and modify and suggest words accordingly. Makes typing faster, easier and more fun. What\'s more, it also supports voice commands, so you don\'t always have to type. Instead, you can speak and your words will be written.<br><br><strong>2. Google Assistant</strong><br><br>Google Assistant is speech recognition software. It records your spoken language as input and produces matching results. Many of us are familiar with Alexa, an Amazon voice recognition model. Likewise, Google Assistant or Google Home is a voice recognition device creation by Google. Besides, it is widely beneficial and is becoming the latest trend. Moreover, it is not only limited to conversation, it can also help you operate various household appliances in your home and act according to your will.</p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/google-input-tools/Google%20Input%20Tools%20%205.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br><strong>3. Google Translate</strong><br><br>Google Translate is a multilingual neural machine translation software that conveniently saves your input in different languages. Also, Google Translate makes it easy to communicate in your preferred language, making it easier for you to use mobile apps and software. Convert your preferred language to any language of your choice, so you don\'t need to learn Hindi or English to work seamlessly on your device, as Google Translate makes it simple with you.<br><br>To read more articles, <a href=\"https://difm.llc/insight/page/1\">click here.</a><br><br></p>', 1, '2021-07-10 09:00:00', '2024-12-19