(120, 'Introduction to Blockchain Technology', 'Blockchain technology has created a truly revolutionary impact. In the automation economy, it is just like a smooth transition between humans and machines. It is just like a distributed digital technology where the history of transactions is unchangeable and visible. It is all possible with the decentralization and hashing of cryptography.', 'bitcoin, blockchain technology, cryptocurrencies', 4, 1, 'https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/Introduction+to+Blockchain+Technology+1.jpg', '<p><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/introduction-to-blockchain-technology/blockchain.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br>Blockchain technology has created a truly revolutionary impact. In the automation economy, it is just like a smooth transition between humans and machines. It is just like a distributed digital technology where the history of transactions is unchangeable and visible. It is all possible with the decentralization and hashing of cryptography.<br><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">History of Blockchain:</strong><br><br>The research starts back in 1980. The first implementation of Blockchain took place in the year 2009, by Satoshi Nakamoto. This first successful transaction took place between the mysterious Satoshi Nakamoto and computer programmer Hal Finney.<br><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">How Does Blockchain Work?</strong><br><br>The three important concepts of Blockchain consist of blocks, nodes, and miners.<br><br>A chain made up of blocks and each block has 3 basic elements include:<br><br><strong style=\"font-size: 18px;\">1. Block data:</strong><br><br>When a block creates, a 32-bit whole number is randomly generated, and so a block header hash generates. A 32-bit whole number called a nonce. To the nonce, the hash is a 256-bit number wedded. With a huge number of zeroes, it must start (i.e., be extremely small). When the first block of a chain creates, the cryptographic hash by a nonce generates. Unless it\'s mined, the data in the block considers forever tied and signed to the nonce and hash.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">2. Miners:</span><br><br>On the chain, miners create new blocks through a process called mining. In a blockchain, every block has its unique hash and nonce. The references include the hash of the previous block in the chain. Especially on large chains, mining a block is not easy. To solve the incredibly complex math problem of finding a nonce that generates an accepted hash, miners use special software. The hash is 256 and the nonce is only 32 bits.<br><br>Before the right one gets found, there will be roughly four billion possible nonce-hash combinations that must be mined. Finally when miners have found the \"golden nonce\" then the block adds to the chain. It requires re-mining before making a change to any block. To manipulate blockchain technology is the only thing that is extremely difficult. It requires an enormous amount of time and computing power to find golden nonce. The change accepts by all of the nodes on the network when a block gets successfully mined. The miner rewards financially once they get success in this mining process.<br><br>Nodes Decentralization is one of the most essential concepts in blockchain technology. Either computer or organization, no one can own the chain. Nodes can be any kind of electronic device that keeps the network functioning and maintains copies of the blockchain a. Every node has a network that must algorithmically approve any newly mined block and its copy of the blockchain for the chain trusted, updated, and verified.<br><br>A unique alphanumeric identification number gives each participant that shows their transactions. A system of balances and checks helps the blockchain maintain the integrity and creates trust among users when combining public information.<br><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Understanding Blockchain with an example</strong><br><br>Understanding blockchain technology let\'s consider a simple analogy with a Google Doc. The document gets distributed, instead of copying or transferring when we create a document and share it with a group of people. Everyone accesses the document at the same time and it creates a decentralized distribution chain that it gives. In a scalable way for myriad uses, it helps reduce risk, stamps out fraud, and brings transparency.<br><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Applications of Blockchain Manufacturing Processes</strong><br><br>To store data from bills of lading for quality inspection records and vehicle components created during the manufacturing process to WIP information for each vehicle assembly from start to finish we can use blockchain.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">1. Finances</span><br><br>The manual data for insertion including transaction variables or transaction costs as well as revisions among other things could be streamlined as all processes. The blockchain will accelerate this process and keep them updated throughout the life cycle of a car.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">2. Vehicle Safety and Data Security:</span><br><br>The more connected a vehicle is the most susceptible it becomes to potentially deadly cyber-attacks.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">3. Telematics:</span><br><br>To keep safe the data received and sent by telematics systems the heightened level of <a href=\"https://searchsecurity.techtarget.com/definition/encryption\" target=\"_blank\">encryption </a>prevents hackers from using or viewing this data we can use blockchain.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Conclusion</span><br><br>Blockchain is one of the most advanced technologies. Whenever a new technology comes then it takes time to build its place. It also takes time for the users to accept it as a reality and use that particular technology. Personal computers, mobiles, tablets, and the internet were some of the technologies that also took time and created their place. To accept blockchain as a reality by people as well as banks may take more years. But one can consider it as a versatile, effective, and safe technology.<br><br>To read more articles, <a href=\"https://difm.llc/insight/page/1\">click here</a></p>', 1, '2021-07-09 09:00:00', '2024-12-19 10:06:44', 'introduction-to-blockchain-technology', ''),
(121, 'Top 5 Google Web Tools and Services', 'Google is well popular for its web services and tools. Our series on Google has covered the basic information on Google tools, Google Tools for all Domains, Best Google Tools for marketers, etc. Moreover, we have also discussed all of these topics in great detail. ', 'chrome, discover, google, internet, playstore, services, tools, web', 7, 1, 'https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/Top+5+Google+Web+Tools+1.jpg', '<p>Google is well popular for its web services and tools. Our series on Google has covered the basic information on Google tools, Google Tools for all Domains, Best Google Tools for marketers, etc. Moreover, we have also discussed all of these topics in great detail.&nbsp;<br><br>Furthermore, in addition to our series on Google, we now present&nbsp;<strong>“Top 5 Google Web Tools and Services”</strong> in detail for you.&nbsp;We are all well acquainted with Google. Google is not merely a search engine or a browser. In fact, Google is a Multinational American Company that offers web services web and models for its users. There is an uncountable number of services that Google offers for its users.<br><br>Google provides a great range of tools and products for its users in all domains, whether it is navigation, entertainment, communication, education, or business, Google never lags. One such domain where Google excels is web services and tools recognized worldwide for their accessibility, availability, feasibility, and applications. Google web services and tools help us connect with the internet every second. Let\'s simplify the term Google web tools by examples- Google Chrome, Gmail, Google Discover, Google Play Store, and the list never ends. Let us discuss the top ten Google web tools in detail.<br><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/top-5-google-web-tools-and-services/Top%205%20Google%20Web%20Tools%202.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br><strong style=\"font-size: 18px;\">1. Google</strong><br><br>Google is an American multinational technology company. Moreover, the Google search engine is the foundation of the company. It is from where it all started. Google was created as a research project by two Ph.D. students studying at Stanford University in California. Google\'s ability to provide immediate best results turned out to be one of the prior reasons for its success.<br><br>Google quickly replaced Yahoo as a search engine and processed 18 million queries in 2000 when it had immediately started. Fast forward to 2021 Google performs approximately 3.8 million queries every minute. Google is the most preferred search engine all across the globe. Every query, every doubt, and every question that comes across our mind, we search it on Google. That itself explains its success and popularity.&nbsp;</p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/top-5-google-web-tools-and-services/Top%205%20Google%20Web%20Tools%203.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">2. Gmail</span><br><br>Gmail is another tool by Google- Google mail which is a free email service provider. The latest stats display that in 2021 Gmail has 1.8 billion active users all across the globe. Now, that is a huge number. Gmail provides 15 GB of storage which is 15 times more than what it promised in 2004 that was 1GB storage capacity. Gmail is a potential tool for communication that is formal or informal. It is safe, reliable, and accessible.<br><br>Gmail has various features and one of them is that it classifies the mail based on its category such as social, promotional, spam, etc. Gmail also enables the use of labels and tags to categorize your emails according to your needs. You can create different labels such as work, personal, office, etc. It is a known mobile application that most of us use for our formal communication, be it education, business, or job.</p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/top-5-google-web-tools-and-services/Top%205%20Google%20Web%20Tools%204.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">3. Google Play Store</span><br><br>Google Play Store is the foremost application that we work on whenever we set up our Androids. All the applications, services, and tools that we pursue on our mobile are accessed by Google Play Store. As the name suggests, it is like an app market for most mobile applications. Starting from games, applications, to books, movies, and music, the Google play store covers it all for you.<br><br>The recent statistics prove that Google Play Store is the one-stop destination for approximately 3 million mobile applications all over the world. Like every other Google tool, the Google play store is safe reliable and easily accessible. Furthermore, it is fast and helps you discover whatever you want to find.</p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/top-5-google-web-tools-and-services/google%20chrome.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">4. Google Chrome</span><br><br>Google Chrome is an internet browser that provides free services. Its official launching took place in December 2008 by Google. It has amazing features that include synchronization, safety, browsing, translation, and spell-check. It is a cross-platform where various queries meet their appropriate solutions. Google Chrome is one of the most popular search browsers. It is very much compatible with Google sites and services.<br><br>One exceptional feature of Google Chrome is the Incognito mode where the search history is not recorded by the website whereas in ordinary Chrome the search history is recorded and the option for saving data and passwords is also available. Any website, link, or search can be done through Google Chrome as it is compatible with most of the tools, websites, and services.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">5. Google Discover</span><br><br>Let\'s simplify it. When you open a Google browser on your phone, the feed that follows below is known as the Google discover. It is a feed experience that keeps you updated and motivated with current affairs. It allows you to discover content that was never in your knowledge before.<br><br>Also, it expands the scope of your knowledge, experience, and information. It displays all the recent updates all over the globe and categorizes them according to your interest and location. Additionally, it never runs out of content that is forever flowing and always new. One of the most attractive features of Google discover is that it is compatible with various languages and it keeps you informed about all the related stories.<br><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Conclusion</strong><br><br>Google LLC is an American Multinational Company that renders web services and tools to its users. Furthermore, tools and services by Google excel in every domain including communication, education, and business. Additionally, it is amongst those companies that deliver the best web services and tools which are easy to use, forever available, and completely reliable. Google browser is the most preferred search engine all over which processes more than 3.8 million queries each minute.<br><br>Furthermore, Google browser, Chrome, Gmail, Play Store, and Google Discover comprise the best 5 Web tools offered by Google. Nonetheless, Google Chrome and Google Search are somewhat similar. They are compatible with almost every safe and authenticated website, source, or address. Gmail is a free email communication service offered by Google that helps us in most of our online formal communication. Google Play Store is the one-stop destination for almost all mobile applications that benefit an Android user. The most underrated of the list is Google Discover which is the feed followed by Google Search. This completes the list.<br><br>To read more articles, <a href=\"https://difm.llc/insight/page/1\">click here.</a></p>', 1, '2021-07-09 09:00:00', '2024-12-19 10:06:44', 'top-5-google-web-tools-and-services', '');
