(122, 'How Web Analytics help Marketing Strategies', 'When it comes to optimizing the online presence of the business, one question arises: how do you know that your business is meeting all objectives, serving the right purpose, or growing? The answer is Google Analytics. It is the digital analytics tool that helps in taking accurate decisions for websites.', 'digital marketing, GOOGLE ANALYTICS, keywords, online presence, pay-per-click, qualified traffic, SEO, Social Media', 6, 1, 'https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/Web+Analytics+help+1.jpg', '<p>When it comes to optimizing the <a href=\"https://bragsocial.com/tips-to-improve-the-online-presence-of-your-business/\" target=\"_blank\">online presence</a> of the business, one question arises: how do you know that your business is meeting all objectives, serving the right purpose, or growing? The answer is Google Analytics. It is the digital analytics tool that helps in taking accurate decisions for websites.&nbsp;<br><br>Google Analytics is a service that is offered by Google that analyses and tracks website traffic. It uses JavaScript code to gather information from websites. Google analytics comes to help business owners to deliver a high-quality website to customers. It also provides all the important information to the owners regarding the website statistics.&nbsp;<br><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Understanding Google Analytics</strong></p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/how-web-analytics-help-marketing-strategies/How%20Web%20Analytics%20help%202.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Google Analytics does not charge you</span><br><br>Google Analytics is the most popular web analytic tool that collects website data. You can use this product for free. Google does not charge you for using this product. You can fetch all the necessary statistics, numbers, and information to maximize your website’s performance. There are many webs analytic tools but most of them provide free services only at the initial stage, they may charge later. Google Analytics is the most efficient and again the free analytical tool that will give you more choices of data analysis.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Collects data automatically</span><br><br>Google Analytics collects the data by default. It collects the pages visited, time of visit, and time spent on each webpage. Hence, it ends up doing all the basic tasks reducing your effort and time. It will provide you with all the basic information you will need to shape the success strategy of your business. Through Google Analytics you will get to discover things that you would have never known about visitors on your site.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Know where your visitors came from</span><br><br>When it comes to knowing the location of your visitors, do not ignore it. You might think what does location has to do with your website’s business. But the geolocation of your visitors matters a lot. Knowing the location will help you set the marketing campaign and goals for that particular area. However, by going deep into the city level you will get more useful information about your audience. Once you get to know where the majority of your audience is located, you can plan accordingly to modify your business for those specific audiences.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Understanding why the visitors are bouncing off your website</span><br><br>You should have a track of your visitors. How many people are visiting your site, who is buying, who is doing window shopping, and how many are leaving the site with disappointment? As soon as you will analyze this you will get to know the bounce rate. Now coming to the bounce rate, it is the percentage of people leaving the site after visiting one page only. You will have to understand the reason behind visitors bouncing off your website to reduce the rate as much as possible. Have a detailed report of your bounce rate and modify your website accordingly.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Learn about search terms that bring in traffic</span><br><br>Google Analytics helps you to determine where your website stands. You must be knowing about search engine optimization and how to bring traffic to your site. But you need to think more than that, increasing the traffic to your site. Use the keyword more often which is bringing the traffic. Try to bring your site on top by improving your on-page SEO. You can also use Google ads for the keyword and start a pay-per-click campaign.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Measuring internal site search under behavior</span><br><br>When you go to site search you will get to know what potential customers are looking for after coming to your website. It provides insights into what people search for on your website. This will show you clear information about the area where you are lacking growth. With this information, you can take necessary actions to change or add the website’s navigation and services offers.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">How Does Google Analytics Help Your Business Website Grow?</span></p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/how-web-analytics-help-marketing-strategies/How%20Web%20Analytics%20help%202.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br>With the above points, you must have got a clear idea about Google analytics and its analyses of your website. Now let us look at how it helps to grow your business website.<br><br>• Google Analytics lets you see the pattern in customers’ behavior. This will help you to get a clear idea of customer, their behavior, and their reaction. Understanding your customer will help you in making informed decisions for the betterment of your website.</p><p><br>• Google Analytics helps you with keywords. It lets you know whether the keyword is leading customers to your site or not. It also tells whether the keyword is leading to conversions in terms of sales. With google analytics, you will get to know them a better understanding of search terms.</p><p><br>• Google Analytics can be integrated with other tools and platforms. It has an easily usable dashboard that makes it more actionable. You can integrate google analytics with all your devices to implement the data easily to other well-known Google products.</p><p><br>• Google Analytics allows you to make a decision on which social media platform to target. This saves up your time. Also, it helps in keeping track of all content that receives views and shares. It individually generates the page views of each content you have posted.&nbsp;</p><p><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Conclusion</strong></p><p><br>If you are managing a website then the use of Google Analytics is a must. The use of Google Analytics can help you in turning up the table of your business. It provides all the needed information which will be beneficial to the business. It gives easy understanding to the business owners of their website’s reach and engagement. Google Analytics is way more beneficial for business websites. By using it you can turn around the fortune of your business. It is a great tool for any online business. It can help you in improving your site, receiving offers, and catching up with your competitions.<br><br>Start using Google Analytics today to gain the advantage and more attention to your site. Look carefully into the data and important metrics to work on.<br><br>To read more articles <a href=\"https://difm.llc/insight/page/1\">click here!</a></p>', 1, '2021-07-02 09:00:00', '2024-12-19 10:06:44', 'how-web-analytics-help-marketing-strategies', ''),
(123, 'Google: A complete guide', 'Google. A name often heard and well known. But what is google? A search engine. Yes. Of course, but is it merely a search engine? No. Google is a lot more than merely a search engine or a browser. It sounds complicated, but is simple. Read this article to understand all about Google.', 'google, growth, guide, history, market, products, tools, vision', 7, 1, 'https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/Google+Complete+Guide+1.jpg', '<p>Google. A name often heard and well known. But what is google? A search engine. Yes. Of course, but is it merely a search engine? No. Google is a lot more than merely a search engine or a browser. It sounds complicated, but is simple. Read this article to understand all about Google.<br><br>Google LLC is an American multinational technology company. LLC stands for Limited Liability Company. This explains that Google can get an assessment distinguishing proof number, open a ledger and work together, and do all such activities, all under its name. In sum, it is a different and particular lawful entity. Google specializes in network-related products and services. In addition, the list also includes online advertising technology, search engines, cloud computing, software, and hardware.&nbsp;</p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/google-a-complete-guide/Google%20Complete%20Guide%202.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Google: History and Vision</strong><br><br>Google was officially established in September 1998 by Larry Page and Sergey Brin at Stanford University in California. The two Ph.D. understudies conjectured about a superior framework that examined the connections among sites since ordinary web indexes positioned results by checking how often the hunt terms showed up on the page. This ability of Google to provide immediate best results turned out to be one of the prior reasons for its success. However, Sundar Pichai replaced Larry Page as Google’s CEO in October 2015.<br><br>Google started as a research project. In 1996, its original name was \"Backrub\". The company has its initial office in Palo Alto, California. It has received funding from many other companies, such as Amazon. In addition, he has also raised capital from several capital companies and other angel investors. The company announced on June 7, 1999, that it would raise $ 25 million. Google quickly replaced Yahoo\'s default search engine. Nonetheless, the company continues to expand its grounds and services.<br><br>Google\'s vision or mission is to<strong>&nbsp;organize the world\'s information and make it universally accessible and useful.</strong> Furthermore, Google believes in accessibility, productivity, and integrity. It aims at providing the best customer satisfaction with exceptional ease.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Google\'s Growth and Market</span><br><br>Google initially started with funding of 25$ million around two decades ago. Fast forward to 2021, the company holds an estimated net worth of 320$ million. Furthermore, it has a market value of 739$ billion. Google comprises one of the four leading internet services- Amazon, Google, Facebook, and Apple. Google processed 18 million searches in 2000. In complete contrast with that, Google had more than 5 billion searches in 2018. Google has grown its market immensely. Here are some interesting facts about Google.<br><br>• Google performs approximately 3.8 million searches every minute.&nbsp;<br>• Globally, Google shares 90.46% of the search market.&nbsp;<br>• In 2017, Google’s Ad revenue summed up to 95.4$ billion.<br>• Furthermore, Google has 2 billion regular users and 500 million users for Google photos<br>• In India, Google holds the market share of 94.39%<br>• On average, Google acquires a company every week. Currently, more than 200 countries are owned by Google and its parent branch Alphabet combined. Sundar Pichai is the current CEO of both companies.&nbsp;<br>• Furthermore, Google’s search engine is believed to grow by 2000% over the last 2 decades.&nbsp;</p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/google-a-complete-guide/Google%20a%20complete%203.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br>All these stats are enough to determine the growth of Google over the years. Google has proved itself as one of the necessities with the help of its exceptional features and services. Let’s have a look at Google’s tools and products.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/google-a-complete-guide/Google%20a%20complete%204.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Products and Services By Google</span><br><br>Google has several services for its users. Furthermore, Google has more than 200 applications and tools to facilitate services to its users. Google has a vast variety of products and tools for all domains. Starting from education to business to expanding its range from marketers and communication, Google moreover has everything. Basic phone management applications. Navigation. Communication. Education. Business. Input tools. Etc. Furthermore, Google does it all for you. You can’t even imagine the number of Google tools and services you use every day. Google hardly lacks something. Here is the list of the most important Google tools for different domains.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Google tools:</span></p><p><br>• <strong>Basic Google Tools for Phone Management:&nbsp;</strong>Clock, Messages, Calculator, Google Phone, Google Calendar, Google Photos, Google Chrome, and Gmail<br>• <strong>Tools by Google for Web Services:&nbsp;</strong>Google, Gmail, Google Chrome, Google Discover, Google Go, Google Play Store, Google News, Google Play Services, and Google Cloud Search<br>• <strong>Google Tools for Entertainment:&nbsp;</strong>Google Play Movies and TV, Google Play Games, Google Play Music, YouTube, Google Podcasts, Google Fit, and Google Home<br>• <strong>Tools for Communication:&nbsp;</strong>Google Duo, Google Hangouts, Google Meet, and Google Chats&nbsp;<br>• <strong>Google Tools for Documentation:&nbsp;</strong>Google Drive, Google, Google Docs, Sheets, and&nbsp;<br>•<strong> Business Tools by Google:</strong>&nbsp;Google My Business, Google Analytics, Google Ads, Currents, Google Sites, and Google Forms<br>• <strong>Google Tools for Navigation:&nbsp;</strong>Google Maps, Google Earth, and Google Streetview<br>• <strong>Google Tools for Education:&nbsp;</strong>Google Books, Google CS First, and Google Classroom<br>• <strong>Input Tools by Google:&nbsp;</strong>Gboard, Google Assistant, and Google Translate<br>• <strong>Other Important Google Tools:</strong> Google Pay, Google Lens, and Google Lookouts<br><br>However, the list does not end here. Google has more tools and applications than even countable. To read more about Google tools and services, read my article “Know All About Google Tools”. Additionally, my article “Google Tools for Marketers” gives a list and overview of almost all Google tools for business and market.&nbsp;</p><p><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Conclusion</strong><br><br>Google LLC is an independent and distinguished American multinational technology company. Furthermore, Google\'s vision or mission is to <strong>organize the world\'s information and make it universally accessible and useful.</strong> It was established in 1998 as a result of the research project done by two Ph.D. students Larry Page and Sergey Brin at Stanford University in California. Alphabet is Google’s parent company. Sundar Pichai is the current CEO of both countries.&nbsp;<br><br>Google’s initial name was “Backrub” and initially, the company had its office in Palo Alto, California. It received funding of 25$ million from different organizations. Nonetheless, Google has grown widely because of its result, versatility, and compatibility. Initially, Google processed 18 million queries in 2000. However, today Google processed 3.8 million queries every minute. That explains its growth and market. Additionally, Google also has several tools, products, and services for its user which contribute majorly to its popularity. To read more articles and know more about Google tools, <a href=\"https://difm.llc/insight/page/1\">click here.&nbsp;</a></p>', 1, '2021-07-02 09:00:00', '2024-12-19 10:06:44', 'google-a-complete-guide', ''),
(124, 'Everything You Need To Know About Google Publisher Center', 'The Google Publisher Center is the new update of Google News Publisher Center which provides valuable changes in a marketing channel. Google has made a point that Google Publisher Center is not a content management system. You can complete the writeups, design as usual, and upload the finished work in the portal. The goal of the Google Publisher Center is to help publishers to manage the content appearance in Google more easily. ', 'content marketing, google news publisher, google ranking, Google tools, SEO', 7, 1, 'https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/Publisher.jpg', '<p>The Google Publisher Center is the new update of Google News Publisher Center which provides valuable changes in a marketing channel. Google has made a point that Google Publisher Center is not a content management system. You can complete the writeups, design as usual, and upload the finished work in the portal. The goal of the Google Publisher Center is to help publishers to manage the content appearance in Google more easily.&nbsp;<br><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">What Is Google Publisher Center?</strong><br><br>Google launched News Publisher Center in 2014. The publisher center is basically an interface where you can publish, manage, and monetize your content in Google News. It links thousands of articles from many publishing organizations and maintains continuous flow. The updated version of&nbsp; Google Publisher Center was launched in mid-December. It merges two Google tools that are Google News Publisher Center and Google News Producer. They altogether provide the best features for users.</p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/everything-you-need-to-know-about-google-publisher-center/Everything%20You%20Need%20To%20Know%20About%20Google%20Publisher%20Center%202.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Functionality</strong><br><br>There are two options available to personalize your publication. For adding the basic information about your publication use the General option. Here you can add details about verification URLs, contact details, and publication location. The other option is Visual Style. Here you can add visual elements like logos and fonts that identify your publication.<br><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Getting Started with Google Publisher Center</strong></p><p><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">1. submit general information</span><br><br>Firstly you will have to start with providing basic information about your profile. This will be needed in verifying your identity. Input all the necessary profile details into Google Publisher.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">2. publishing content</span><br><br>You will not directly publish your content on Google Publisher. Instead, you will use the content tab to inform Google where your content is and how it should be categorized. Then you can go for adding sections. This will make sure that content appears under specific tabs in Google News. Now add the labels to highlight specific areas of your websites. Labels include satire, blog, press release, opinion, and user-generated.&nbsp;<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">3. Add image</span><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">s</span><br><br>It is the option where you upload or add different versions of your logo. With this, you can add your logo in the images tab of the Google Publisher center.&nbsp;<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">4. Ads</span><br><br>Google News allows its user to run ads. You can use Adsense to your account if you are looking to monetize. But keep in mind to not add too many ads to your content. Also, Google recommends using a strategy known as flexible sampling which offers limited access to the visitors. This way visitors can easily crawl into your site and get to know more about your brand.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">5. Review and Publish your content</span><br><br>With the review and preview option, you can do the final check on your content. You can also preview the draft and check on the issues that can cause any trouble.&nbsp;<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">6. Advanced settings</span><br><br>There is a tab available named “Advanced” that allows you a handful of tools for testing variations. Settings like user permission with which you can control the account access, account settings that allow you to add, edit, or delete accounts, and account settings that will provide appropriate settings for your organization.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Google News Ranking Factors</span><br><br>When it comes to organic search Google News almost follows the same procedure used to rank search results. Google goes into more detail for examining the relevance and quality of content. The major factors that Google news determines algorithmically are prominence, the relevance of content, uniqueness, language, authority, and location. The Newsstand tab that is created by the Google staff, helps users to discover new sources according to their interests. However, quality matters most in the content. Apart from this, there are eligibility criteria that you will need to meet in order to get your content published in Google New. Let us look into the following eligibility criteria:<br><br>• Google has its own policy. Your content must not go against Google’s content policy. It should not contain baseless claims, harassment, false allegations, or plagiarized content.&nbsp;<br>• It should follow Google’s content and design guidelines. That is to create useful information, accurately describe your content, and do not add more links on a page.<br>• If you are publishing video content then it must meet the standard listed guidelines of the Youtube community.<br>• Your site should follow Google’s site requirements. Crawl’s path should be easy and secure for bots to navigate.<br><br>In the documentation provided by Google, it mentioned that the new sites must go through E-A-T which means expertise, authoritativeness, and trustworthiness. Evaluating content and websites for Google news is a critical observation for E-A-T than that of other Google searches. Google news emphasizes higher content quality. If your content is good your content is more likely to appear at the top.</p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/everything-you-need-to-know-about-google-publisher-center/Everything%20You%20Need%20To%20Know%20About%20Google%20Publisher%20Center%203.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Tracking Your Performance</span><br><br>There are a couple of ways through which you can track content performance inside the Google Publisher Center. Also, you can use a Google Analytics account with the rest of your traffic.&nbsp;<br><br>For content submission use RSS feed so that you can track the performance through <a href=\"http://www.google.com/\" target=\"_blank\">www.google.com</a> or <a href=\"www.url.google.com\">www.url.google.com</a> referrers. You can also set up tracking inside your publisher to know more about how users are interacting with your content. As suggested by Google, do not combine feed analytics numbers from the publisher center and referees as they perform the same task. So this may result in spoiling the entire data set.</p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/everything-you-need-to-know-about-google-publisher-center/Everything%20You%20Need%20To%20Know%20About%20Google%20Publisher%20Center%204.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Conclusion&nbsp;</span><br><br>Google news is a great way to get new readers without paying for additional ads. With the update in google news, Google has made it more efficient for publishers. Google Publisher Center is a great interface for publishers to share their content. The new update has technically made it possible for content from any site to appear in Google news. However, Google is strict with its policies and requirements. If you are looking to grab the new opportunity to publish your exceptional content, Google Publisher Center is a way to get more mileage.<br><br>For more articles <a href=\"https://difm.llc/insight/page/1\" target=\"_blank\">click here!</a></p>', 1, '2021-07-02 09:00:00', '2024-12-19 10:06:44', 'everything-you-need-to-know-about-google-publisher-center', ''),
(125, 'What\'s new in Microsoft Office?  ', 'In-Office 2019, Office 365, and Microsoft 365 subscribers always have the latest version of Microsoft Office. With a subscription, they also get more frequent software updates than those who have purchased Office 2019 without a subscription, which means subscribers have access to the security patches, latest features, and bug fixes.', 'microsoft, new features, office 365, windows 11', 7, 1, 'https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/Microsoft+unveiling+the+Windows+1.jpg', '<p>In-Office 2019, Office 365, and Microsoft 365 subscribers always have the latest version of Microsoft Office. With a subscription, they also get more frequent software updates than those who have purchased Office 2019 without a subscription, which means subscribers have access to the security patches, latest features, and bug fixes.<br><br>To keep track of the changes in each update, it can be hard and know when they are available. Connected with all apps and services, both to each other and to the wider web, saving employees time, facilitating teamwork, and enabling them to work better together. Through tools such as team chat, co-authoring, online meetings, and sharing files, and group emails with Office 365. The inclusion of cloud storage and mobile apps in the Office 365 suite also allows organizations to work wherever, with secure access to content, whenever, tasks, conversations, and schedules from any device.<br><br>So today, we are going to discuss some of these amazing features and changes that will take place.<br><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">&nbsp;Microsoft Core apps and services<br></strong><br>The leading producer of technology is core apps. The first cloud application is Office 365. Office 365 hosts on Microsoft servers all applications, services, and data generated. The facility of email storage and cloud capacity provides by Office 365.</p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/microsoft-unveiling-the-windows-11/Microsoft%20unveiling%20the%20Windows%20.2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br></p><p>A hot-button topic for organizations across all industries with data security, many businesses choose Office 365 because of its layered security measures, privacy protection, proactive data monitoring, and 99.9% uptime service level agreement.<br><br>Further, is the list of core apps and services with their information:<br><br><strong>1.) Microsoft Word<br></strong><br>In the autumn of 1983, the primary version of Word releases, for the MS-DOS software system and introduced the pc mouse to more users. For Mac, it launched in 1985. It\'s an application included in Microsoft Office. Microsoft Word\'s first graphical version was Word for Mac. Word was first to introduce the Support for Portable Document Format (PDF) and OpenDocument (ODF) with Service Pack 2 for Word 2007.<br><br><strong>2.) Microsoft Excel<br></strong><br>Microsoft Excel is additionally called spreadsheet editor. In the beginning, Microsoft Excel competed with the Lotus 1-2-3 and eventually outsold it. In 1985 Microsoft released the primary version of Excel for the Mac OS and also the first Windows version (numbered 2.05 to line up with the Mac) in November 1987.<br><br><strong>3.) Microsoft PowerPoint<br></strong><br>Microsoft PowerPoint could be a presentation program accustomed create slideshows composed of graphics, text, and other objects. It often shows the presenter and is displayed on-screen or printed out on transparencies or slides. In front of the audience easily and practically it helps people to better understand the topic or idea.<br><br><strong>4.) Microsoft OneNote<br></strong><br>Microsoft OneNote could be a notetaking program that gathers typed notes or handwritten, screen clippings, drawings, and audio commentaries. Over the net or a network, notes, shared with other OneNote users. Initially, it launched as a standalone app. In any Microsoft Office 2003 edition, it\'s provided. In-Office on the online, a freemium (and later freeware) Windows desktop app, a mobile app for Windows Phone, Android, iOS, and Symbian, and a Metro-style app for Windows 8 or later.<br><br><strong>5.) Microsoft Outlook<br></strong><br>Microsoft Outlook must not befuddle with Outlook Express, Outlook.com, or Outlook online. Starting in Office 97, Microsoft Outlook could be a personal information manager that replaces Windows Messaging, Microsoft Mail, and Schedule+. But it did be just for use with Microsoft Exchange Server.<br><br><strong>6.) Microsoft OneDrive<br></strong><br>Microsoft OneDrive allows users to sync files and later access them from a mobile device or applications program. It is a file hosting service. Skype for Business is an integrated communications client for meetings in real-time and conferences; it is the sole Microsoft Office desktop app that neither has the \"Microsoft\" prefix in its name nor useful without a correct network infrastructure. Microsoft Teams could be a platform that mixes workplace chat, notes, meetings, and attachments. For replacing Skype for Business, Microsoft announced that Teams would eventually.</p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/microsoft-unveiling-the-windows-11/Microsoft%20unveiling%20the%20Windows%203.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Latest Update of the Office 365<br></strong><br>Version 2107 (Build 14217.20002) |June 25, 2021<br><br>Outlook Default and mandatory labeling improvements Microsoft has now improved the functionality for mandatory and functionality labeling in Outlook. Outlook clients used built-in labeling. But now, Outlook clients will enforce the existing PowerShell label policy advanced settings DisableMandatoryInOutlook and OutlookDefaultLabel. Previously supported only by the <a href=\"https://azure.microsoft.com/en-i\" target=\"_blank\">Azure </a>Information Protection unified labeling client. Notable Fixes When composing a message in a right-to-left language hyperlinks, including digits, broke issue fixed.<br><br><strong>Word Notable fixes</strong></p><p><br>•&nbsp;When enabling auto-save could cause recent edits to temporarily disappear issue fixed.<br>• Scrolling in the comments, pane issue fixed.<br>•&nbsp;When header/footer text was not visible in print preview, the office theme was set to black fixed.</p><p><br><strong>Excel Notable Fixes</strong></p><p><br>•&nbsp;When chart axis values could not alter if both the thousand and decimal separators use the same symbol fixed.</p><p><br><strong>&nbsp;PowerPoint Notable fixes</strong></p><p><br></p><p>•&nbsp;Related to SmartArt nodes having Change Shape disabled fixed.</p><p><br><strong>Project Notable fixes</strong></p><p><br>•&nbsp;The Project client desktop engagements created in the Project Web App might not load properly if the resource name had special characters, such as a semicolon fixed.<br>•&nbsp;The time-phased cost values might not have been correctly baselined for cost-type resources when the project option \"Project should calculate costs” disables fixed.<br>•&nbsp;Project desktop client project-level enterprise custom fields with lookup tables were not showing a value fixed.<br>•&nbsp;Saving a local project to Project Web App could change a previously saved baseline fixed.</p><p><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Conclusion:</span><br><br>Office 365 is useful for the growth of businesses too. The essential tasks such as sharing documents, knowledge, editing, communicating, planning, and processing data can perform better with the help of Office 365. With the help of Office 365, businesses can create, innovate, grow their business faster and give growth for the organization rapidly. It is convenient and cost-effective.&nbsp; 1 TB of OneDrive for Business cloud storage included for each user in Office 365 subscriptions. Enterprise E3 and E5 plan to receive unlimited cloud storage provided in Office 365. Office 365 provides a boost memory availability,&nbsp;and a faster experience.<br><br>To read more article, <a href=\"https://difm.llc/insight/page/1\">click here</a><br><br></p>', 1, '2021-07-02 09:00:00', '2024-12-19 10:06:44', 'whats-new-in-microsoft-office', ''),
(126, 'An Overview Of Google Webmaster Tools', 'For any business website, it is important to succeed online, enhancing the site’s SEO and exercising good practices. Fitting Google Webmaster Tools for your website helps you to urge found online by your customers. It is a free resource for web designers offering data and configuration control for your website. GWT could be a useful gizmo to get an issue that is hindering the expansion of your website. With GWT you will be able to better understand the website’s needs.', '	business website, GOOGLE ANALYTICS, Google tools, search console, SEO', 7, 1, 'https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/An+Overview+Of+Google+Webmaster+Tools+4.jpg', '<p>For any business website, it is important to succeed online, enhancing the site’s SEO and exercising good practices. Fitting Google Webmaster Tools for your website helps you to urge found online by your customers. It is a free resource for web designers offering data and configuration control for your website. GWT could be a useful gizmo to get an issue that is hindering the expansion of your website. With GWT you will be able to better understand the website’s needs.<br><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">What Is Google Webmaster Tools<br></strong><br>Google webmaster tools is a web service provided by Google to test and optimize the status of the websites. The Google Webmaster Tools or the Google search console offers valuable services to the website’s admin. It helps you to stay up together with your website by identifying issues. It provides keen details of the website’s engagement by allowing you to watch various activities of the website. GWT also alerts you when your site is infected with malware.<br><br>With Google Webmaster Tools, Google communicates with website admin if anything goes the wrong sort of a page not found, miscalculation occurred in a very page, manual penalties, a rise in 404 pages, etc. You\'ll not use any paid tools for your website once you begin using Google Webmaster Tools. GWT rectifies any problems and ensures the <a href=\"https://bragsocial.com/tips-to-improve-the-online-presence-of-your-business/\" target=\"_blank\">website runs smoothly</a>. Because the GWT is completely free it\'s quite difficult to grasp its acting at first. Allow us to take time and understand Google webmaster tools intimately.</p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/an-overview-of-google-webmaster-tools/An%20Overview%20Of%20Google%20Webmaster%201.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">How To Start With Google Webmaster Tools</span><br><br>The first thing you may need to do is sign up for the Google Webmaster Tools account. As soon as you sign up you will be entered into your website’s details.<br><br><strong><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Verification</span><br></strong><br>Verification is important for your website. Verifying will make sure that you own the website. Through the method of verification, you become the authorized representative of your site. In this manner, no other party is going to be able to access your website data.<br><br><strong style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Uploading HTML file and Using HTML tag<br></strong><br>To verify your site with an HTML file, download the GWT blanks HTML file. Drop the basis directory of your site in it and click on on the verify button. You may get access to Google Webmaster Tools data for your site. Also, GWT provides you with a meta tag that you simply can use for verification. Copy and paste that meta tag and insert it into the top of your home page. Now click on the verify button and it is done.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">Add name Provider</span><br><br>Now it is time to urge the name provider. Select the drop-down list and choose your provider. Google will send you a singular verification code. Together with that Google sends an instruction. Follow that instruction step by step.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">Use Google Analytics and Google Tag Manager</span><br><br>If your Google account is that the same for both GWT and Google Analytics then you will verify your ownership of the positioning using tracking mode. And you will be able to also use Google Tag Manager for verifying your site. Except for this, you may need permission to manage the Task Manager container.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">Working With Google Webmaster Tools Dashboard</span><br><br>After you are finished the verification, you are all able to start examining the information of your site.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">Site Setting</span><br><br>Through site setting, you\'ll select your target country. you will set the frequency at which you would like Google bots to index your site. Here you will inform Google about any information about your website is in a different way than you simply were missing out on earlier information.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">Webmaster Tools Preferences</span><br><br>Here you will be able to make the settings whether you would like to receive daily notifications or not, and you will choose your email contact. Also, you will be able to set your preferred language.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">Change address</span><br><br>If you are making any changes to your site or moving your site to a replacement domain you head to change of address and inform Google.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">Google Analytics property</span><br><br>Here you will be able to link your Google Analytics account together with your GWT account in order that you\'ll be able to access the information from both accounts. If you are doing not have a Google Analytics account, you will be able to create one here.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">Users and Site owners</span><br><br>Here you will manage who can edit and have access to the GWT account. a replacement user will be added if needed. Admin has permission to access the positioning when. Users with “full” permission can do everything except changing address, adding users, and linking GA accounts. Users with “restricted” permission only have viewing capabilities.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 18px;\">Verification details and Associates</span><br><br>Verification details inform you about any verification issues and successful attempts. And therefore the Associates enables you to link your GA account to your GWT account.</p><p><br><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/an-overview-of-google-webmaster-tools/An%20Overview%20Of%20Google%20Webmaster%20Tools%202.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Benefits Of Google Webmaster Tools</span><br><br>One of the simplest benefits of GWT is that it is totally unengaged to use. With GWT you will be able to make sure that you are running an efficient and healthy website. Allow us to cross-check some more benefits of Google Webmaster Tools.<br><br>• You will have the access to go looking for any statistics on Google.<br>• GWT will keep you updated with the newest data regarding incoming links and internal links.<br>• You will get instant notifications if your site is infected by malware or has any crawl errors.<br>• It will show you the duplicate pages and meta descriptions.<br>• GWT helps your site to point out up in Google search results.<br>• Quickly updates your content in order that it can show up in search results faster.</p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/an-overview-of-google-webmaster-tools/An%20Overview%20Of%20Google%20Webmaster%20Tools%203.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Conclusion<br></strong><br>Google Webmaster Tools is a tremendous <a href=\"https://difm.tech/know-all-about-google-tools\" target=\"_blank\">Google tool</a> that helps you to grasp what is happening on the website. If you would like to stay up along with your business website then it is a requirement to use GWT. It will not only facilitate your detection issues but also will help your site is running efficiently. GWT holds the facility to try to do many things. It is the foremost beneficial feature. Once you get to understand the functioning of Google Webmaster Tools, you may be better at handling the general health of your website.<br><br>For more articles <a href=\"https://difm.llc/insight/page/1\">click here!</a></p>', 1, '2021-06-30 09:00:00', '2024-12-19 10:06:44', 'an-overview-of-google-webmaster-tools', '');
