(132, 'Top 10 NASA Inventions That We Use Today', '“Inventions are the most important product of man\'s creative brain. The ultimate purpose is the complete mastery of mind over the material world, the harnessing of human nature to human needs.”', '	future, innovation, inventions, nasa, technology', 7, 1, 'https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/Top+10+NASA+Inventions+That+We+Use+Today.jpg', '<p>“Inventions are the most important product of man\'s creative brain. The ultimate purpose is the complete mastery of mind over the material world, the harnessing of human nature to human needs.”<br><br>― Nikola Tesla<br><br>Inventions are intriguing. They give rise to technology and advancements that make lives easier and better. It does not matter if your invention is small or big, all that matters is that you invented something, and it matters because inventions represent your ideas, creativity, and vision.<br><br>National Aeronautics and Space Administration, more commonly known as NASA in an independent research organization. It is an agency for the US federal government responsible for civilian space programs. However, the organization has earned fame all over the world because of its marvelous work and creations. It excels in space research and aviation. Let’s have a look at the top ten inventions of NASA that are useful in our day-to-day life.<br><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">1. Long Distance Telecommunication<br></strong><br>\"This technology has the potential to create a better world,\"<br><br>- Jan Wittry (SGT- NASA\'s Glenn Research Center)<br><br>One of NASA\'s genius creations is satellites that could speak with individuals on the ground about space resemblance before people were sent into space. It was executed with the use of comparable satellite innovation consisting of around 200 correspondence satellites circle the globe every day. Imparting across huge spans is consistently a test. To solve this problem, NASA is creating extraordinary communication systems that assist individuals with interfacing distance without any problem which are functional for the past many years.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">2. The Invention of Artificial Limbs</span><br><br>Progress in technical mechanics causes artificial limbs to work more like a genuine article. When the muscle is not functional, these are beneficial to keep the blood streaming around the heart. A result of cooperation between NASA, MicroMed Technology Inc, and researchers; the VAD is the discovery of artificial limbs which has changed the life of many individuals. One of their exploration instruments is a PC program. NASA is popular for its initial creation. It is designed to recognize surface highlights in Landsat picture handling across the globe. Furthermore, the clinical world refers to the creation of counterfeit appendages as prosthetics.</p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/top-10-nasa-inventions-that-we-use-today/Top%2010%20NASA%20Inventions%20That%20We%20Use%20Today%201%20copy.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">3. Solar Cells</span><br><br>A solar cell is an electrical gadget that changes over the energy of light into power by the photovoltaic impact. NASA also studied solar cells as an electrical contraption that changes over the energy of light directly into power by the photovoltaic effect, which is a physical and manufactured miracle. Solar cells are important as they renew energy and are economy and environment-friendly.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">4. The Inventions of PCs, Mouse, Cordless Tools, and Camera Phones</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\"><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/top-10-nasa-inventions-that-we-use-today/Top%2010%20NASA%20Inventions%20That%20We%20Use%20Today%202%20copy.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"></span><br><br>We are all aware of modern-day innovations. Personal Computers more commonly known as PCs have become essential in this virtual world. Almost every work is carried out through our PCs and it becomes unimaginable to work on PCs without the mouse. Also, phone cameras have made it easy to capture moments. Cordless tools enable us to work without any limitation according to our comfort zones.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">5. The Inventions of Pool Water Purification and Filters</span><br><br>Pure water is the world’s first and foremost medicine.</p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/top-10-nasa-inventions-that-we-use-today/Top 10 NASA Inventions That We Use Today 3 copy.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br></p><p>The thought of swim intrigue and excites everyone. However, pool water usually gets impure. The use of ionization for water cleaning is popular since the 60s by NASA. Caribbean Clear consolidated this innovation and fostered an ionization item for acquainting both copper and silver with pool water. Copper is a notable algaecide and silver has the extraordinary enemy of microbial properties. Adding further to it, NASA also created water filters that provide pure, good quality drinkable water. NASA helps in water purification and optimization and fostered a filtration gadget to wipe out pollutants from water supplies and filter wastewater for reuse. We all are aware of the importance of water so we should judiciously use water and conserve it for the further generations.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">6. Inventions of LED</span><br><br>LED lights fulfill many purposes including efficiency, versatility, and compatibility. NASA has developed LEDs that are beneficial for various purposes. One reason is business plant development research on space transport that is beneficial to eliminate mind tumors through photodynamic treatment. Furthermore, NASA Light Technology successfully reduces cancer patients\' painful side effects from radiation and chemotherapy.</p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/top-10-nasa-inventions-that-we-use-today/Top%2010%20NASA%20Inventions%20That%20We%20Use%20Today%204%20copy.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\"><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">7. Open Stack</span><br><br>Open source is gaining immediate and fast recognition in the evolving world today. The open-source project presently known as OpenStack is a creation by NASA and Rackspace Inc. OpenStack is a free, open standard distributed computing stage. Additionally, the product stage comprises different parts and the non-profit OpenStack Foundation oversees that. Besides, it is beneficial to innumerable organizations and examination associations, including a considerable lot of the world\'s most unmistakable brands, to deal with their information.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">8. Insulation</span><br><br>Insulation plays out a few significant capacities in your home. Basically, insulation is material intended to keep warmth or sound from being communicated starting with one region then onto the next. NASA\'s advancement materials can altogether affect numerous perspectives including pipelines, safeguards, covers, fridges, and so on NASA\'s insulation materials range from aerogels and natural polymers to phenolic-impregnated carbon ablators and powder-filled protecting layers.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">9. Precision GPS</span><br><br>Global Positioning System more commonly known as GPS defines and tracks our location. It helps us to stay connected or find new routes when we travel to different places. However, it also requires an active internet connection. NASA enables you to use GPS technology even without the availability of a connection. The Jet Propulsion Laboratory created precision GPS with information spilled from its worldwide organization of GPS beneficiaries. Also, NASA states that many people and organizations use this technology globally.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">10. Inventions of Ear Thermometers</span><br><br>An ear thermometer is a hand-held gadget that reads the temperature. It is also known as Aural thermometers. It sidesteps more intrusive estimating strategies while giving precise temperature readings and works by estimating the warmth delivered from the eardrum in the inward ear. In sum, infrared innovation is utilized to gauge the temperature of the stars. Also, a similar innovation is beneficial in-ear thermometers.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Conclusion</span><br><br>NASA is an independent space research organization of the US which expertise in inventions and aviation concerning space. Some of the best NASA inventions that we all know and are also beneficial in our day-to-day life are long-distance telecommunication facilities, precision GPS, water filters, PCs, phone cameras, insulation, open stack, etc. Moreover, the list is never-ending.<br><br></p>', 1, '2021-06-16 09:00:00', '2024-12-19 10:06:45', 'top-10-nasa-inventions-that-we-use-today', ''),
(133, 'LIFE BEYOND EARTH- In Search of Possibilities', 'Life beyond the earth has always been a fascinating topic. Some believe in aliens living on other planets, some predict a mirror world. Till now all we know is there exist other planets and we are not alone in the universe. Scientists have stepped into the outer world in search of life. The word “life” itself is undefined. We only know where there is water, there is life. According to a report from the National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA), water has been found on Mars.', '	land rover, nasa, outer space, solar system, technosignatures', 5, 1, 'https://difm.s3-eu-central-2.ionoscloud.com/blogs/LIFE+BEYOND+EARTH-+In+Search+of+Possibilities.jpg', '<p>Life beyond the earth has always been a fascinating topic. Some believe in aliens living on other planets, some predict a mirror world. Till now all we know is there exist other planets and we are not alone in the universe. Scientists have stepped into the outer world in search of life. The word “life” itself is undefined. We only know where there is water, there is life. According to a report from the National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA), water has been found on Mars.&nbsp;<br><br>Since the beginning, humans have questioned the existence of life other than Earth. NASA has developed advanced tools to explore the solar system and beyond to find the existence of life. Life on Earth can survive under harsh conditions has helped scientists in broadening the understanding of where they might find life in the solar system. Scientists are expanding their ideas and trying to find what kind of worlds support life.<br><br><strong style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Life In The Outer Solar System<br></strong><br>This is for sure that planets Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, and Neptune are not habitable for life. They receive warming sunlight and contain abundant water. There is one interesting fact about Jupiter and its moon. When the moon orbits Jupiter the massive gravity creates tides and generates water in liquid form.&nbsp;<br><br>Europa, Jupiter’s moon, has an ocean but not life. There is a thick ice crust in Europa through which sunlight is not able to penetrate. Hence, there is no energy and life.&nbsp;<br><br>Saturn’s moon Enceladus made a remarkable discovery of salt and icy material. It has been suggested that the source of the ocean water is present in Enceladus. Although there is no possibility that it is home to live.&nbsp;<br><br>The unusual chemistry of Saturn’s big moon Titan makes it an interesting place. Titan is composed of nitrogen, 5% of methane, and also a variety of complex organic compounds. It has liquid water deep within its interior. The liquid actually can not be called water. The liquid is maybe made of hydrocarbons such as ethane and methane.<br><br>Let us dig more into exoplanets. Defining exoplanets, it is a planet that is outside of our solar system. The exoplanets Kepler-62f, Kepler-186f, and Kepler-442b are found to have the potential of having a life. Kepler-1649c and earth are somewhat similar. The size and an estimated temperature of Kepler01649c are similar to earth. However, this world is 300 light-years away from earth. The presence of water there also gives a sign of the presence of life. This newly found world is 1.06 times larger than the earth. There are more than 170 solar systems. And over two hundred more extrasolar planets.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Life On Mars</span><br><br>Mars is closest to the earth. Hence, we explore it more. But still, we do not know much about it. According to NASA, exploring Mars will help us to get the answer to the origin and existence of life. Mars is different from other planets. It has a climate and atmosphere and like earth, change in the climate has been noticed over its history. So the chances of having a life there increase. The environment of Mars has drastically changed over the years. Today it is not what it was in past years. Scientists believe that Mars has the capability to nurture life. Mars shows signs that microbial lives may have lived there billions of years ago.<br><br>In 1996, Dr. David McKay with his team of scientists found the fossils of bacteria. Later, NASA scientists took help from a robotic Mars rover to research more on Mars. Due to the similarities of Mars and Earth, Mars has always been the subject of interest. However, the surface of Mars is not supportable for humans. The radiation reduced air pressure, and lower oxygen is the reasons Mars is not favorable for the survival of humans.&nbsp;<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Search For Technological Life</span><br><br>For finding extraterrestrial life scientists use advanced technology that is capable of detecting the signs of alien technology or biological signatures of life. Humans now have technological reach to other plants in search of life.<br><br>Technosignatures are a signal which is used for researching the existence of technological life in the universe. The term techno signatures are used for defining the search for extraterrestrial intelligence. One such techno signature is radio signals. Humans have been drifting radios and satellites into space for several years. Scientists are now taking a keen interest in proving the existence of technological life. But it will take them more investments and more than unexplained signals.<br><br>NASA is constantly supporting new projects to search for signs of technology in the universe that may lead them to evidence of intelligent life. The distance and travel time involved in sending human crews to Mars or missions beyond are too great. Landing rovers and robotic space probes are instruments that are capable of exploring a huge distance and providing wealthy information.&nbsp;<br><br>The existence of aliens has always been questioned. Over the years many claimed to spot the UFO but none was proved. So we can say that Earth has not been visited by any intelligent aliens yet. The Kepler space telescope has found many new worlds. Ever Since it has helped in search of aliens.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 24px;\">Conclusion&nbsp;</span><br><br>Researchers are trying their best to find life in the solar system. Water alone is not enough for having a life. It involves chemical ingredients such as carbon, nitrogen, oxygen, phosphorus,&nbsp; hydrogen, and sulfur. Together they stir up and look for a source of energy.<br><br>Space technology has improved a lot over time. This improvement has led to the discovery of new planets. There are a lot of things beyond earth that we do not know. Science is all about figuring out the “why”.&nbsp;<br><br>Scientists and researchers are working hard together intending to find signs of life beyond earth. Hunt for life elsewhere in the universe will be forever.&nbsp;<br><br>For more articles<a href=\"https://difm.llc/insight/page/1\"> click here.<br></a><br></p>', 1, '2021-06-16 09:00:00', '2024-12-19 10:06:45', 'life-beyond-earth-in-search-of-possibilities', '');
